document.title: Early Learning Standards Framework Content Standards and Learning Criteria for West Virginia Pre-Kindergarten

49BA251D93334D98825BD4BF40A42FEB.description: Follows classroom and community safety rules, such as fire drills, traffic and pedestrian safety, and responding appropriately to potentially harmful objects, substances, and activities.

5983309277394DE3B61ED34943798481.description: Participates in safety games, songs and stories.

088247F4C9574A1EBD1EC06C0B88D501.description: Demonstrates an understanding of the need for different apparel in different climates and weather conditions.

7F278C4408304B50A229CFD4124FFAD0.description: Demonstrates growing independence in daily health routines and habits in hygiene, nutrition and personal care when eating, dressing, washing hands, brushing teeth, and toileting.

B6706EC713AC4934A6583FEDAD486338.description: Exhibits increased physical growth, strength, stamina, endurance and flexibility.

5F6CB6AA3455414B9AAEB207FC70AFD5.description: Participates actively in games, outdoor play and other forms of exercise that enhances physical fitness.

BA8ABF6CC08A4F45894567F7E990717E.description: Demonstrates ability to identify and make healthy food choices.

849A8B66CA764AB78EE68C15796B7712.description: Moves with emergent balance on lines, balance beams, curbs, riding equipment, and play structures.

85B803AB1DF94142A4ACB38733D31ED1.description: Demonstrates increased abilities to coordinate movements in throwing, catching, kicking, bouncing balls, and ascending and descending stairs.

5DC6E937C73548D8ADEF728B2668E11F.description: Demonstrates increased control and proficiency in walking, running, jumping, hopping, skipping, marching, and galloping.

57FA44E04EC24DFAACDF354AE17953F4.description: Begins to demonstrate self help skills such as buttoning and zipping.

8516A3275E744855A7C96D3B58CB15AE.description: Progress in ability to use writing, drawing and art tools, including pencils, markers, chalk, paint brushes, and various types of technology.

AD408D5C1CF64461B3B23C894876B1AC.description: Demonstrates increased accuracy of eye-hand coordination and use of opposing hand movements to build with blocks, string beads, cut with scissors, or put together puzzles.

36C86F79954D430CA232C2A47C75E3B7.description: Demonstrates increased ability, strength, dexterity, and control to manipulate and use tools such as scissors, staplers, hammers, and fastening tools.

32ED78EF6687456BACE0CB2ACA68CC4B.description: Tells and re-enacts stories and experiences through dramatic play.

C0D87DF733DE470F80541B7076088DAE.description: Shows growing creativity and imagination in using materials and assuming roles, e.g. interaction with costume pieces, props, puppets, fabric, etc.

8F86C0DA667743BBB76341163A0BCCBD.description: Expresses ideas, feelings, and emotions through dramatic play.

E0D0E875D0C347F1B2AC53BE217FB277.description: Participates in a variety of dramatic play activities throughout the day in a variety of settings that becomes more extended and complex.

B3DFC0CE11FF47ED947D6E5CE7797876.description: Begins to demonstrate increased detail in a variety of artwork, including drawings, paintings, models, and other multi-dimensional artwork.

E8D8AE15C3734A8187BE0F65B3BC9B6E.description: Explores color and texture using different mediums, including clay, natural materials, wood, paper, crayons, chalk, paint, glue, paste, etc.

CF206EF826644071930B5328637EB199.description: Develops growing ability to create artwork that reflects an idea, theme, or story.

E58EA3C5782C4A93A5B9D84C2EA17BC0.description: Demonstrates growing ability to plan, work independently, and demonstrate care and persistence in a variety of art project.

428159CC04584343928E0EAF9F6001CE.description: Progresses in ability to express emotion and communicates ideas through creative artwork.

D00A68B194884404AB106ED84D43D0B9.description: Responds to and indentifies particular musical elements such as rhythm and style.

A13002FFB27343CEAEC5D90E0C295138.description: Uses a variety of instruments including non-traditional and natural objects.

5FED29640E3C4DBC9B2BE320F47018E3.description: Demonstrates an understanding of movement as it relates to music.

433C08BCA02C4ACBA8350B753C17BB39.description: Creates music through a variety of techniques.

1B61C610A30E4ADD847E690D2B5B0F0E.description: Participates in music activities, including listening, singing and finger plays.

EA9190923F144C348511BBE9EE5CA337.description: Demonstrates expanding knowledge of and respect for the environment.

A800878220964D2793AB076534056E92.description: Shows increased awareness and beginning understanding of changes in materials and cause-effect relationships, such as recognize that materials can exist in several physical states.

353E6E19098B4BADB41F6B5221003283.description: Observes and describes the immediate and familiar world, such as the natural world, materials, living things, and natural processes.

1FC151DDC9134B05A714C5EBDD70D8A6.description: Understanding the living and physical world

1BA86D8A8A4A4008AC6103C072E5F4CF.description: Collects, describes, and records information through a variety of means to lead to new understanding of the world around them.

91AB08F722884729BB3EEC17958676BF.description: Uses senses and a variety of tools to gather information, investigate materials, and observe processes and relationships

AE562B1D3A0949CCAC5740FACF44A930.description: Progresses in ability to describe and discuss predictions, explanations, and generalizations.

CBB85F2BCA42437C8FF8C02DADF21935.description: Investigates and problem solves through active exploration of the environment.

2633CA78D5A446F29FCEA66D5B358681.description: Recognizes, describes, compares, and names common shapes.

EA6289966DBE49C5B74DF6B8DB659084.description: Progresses in ability to recognize terms of directionality, order, and positions of themselves and objects in their environment, such as up, down, over, under, top, bottom, inside, outside, in front, and behind.

9835C361616D4A1EBCFEA8F86D753CBF.description: Recognizes, duplicates, and creates simple patterns using a variety of materials.

6128747C760E4FFB9301DB594B417E43.description: Shapes, their attributes, and spatial reasoning

5B36D683B6CF48C497C0DAC8E5408A01.description: Begins to recognize and interpret information presented in tables, graphs and symbols.

5D43458A270C41D7AC1F66F22DB27D9A.description: Begins to incorporate estimating and measuring activities into play.

04EE249FE5054C638C149DC05CD29448.description: Classify objects according to common characteristics, such as color, size, or shape.

DCDDD8E017D94ED2AE1E02FED9C08F42.description: Begins to construct a sense of time through participation in daily activities.

FD2F418AE6E043488399EC02749E264A.description: Estimates the size of objects in comparison to a common unit of measurement, such as more/less, short/tall, long/short, big/little, and light/heavy.

50E5DD2D67DF4BFDB29CCC9B783B26B2.description: Understand that objects have measurable attributes, such as length or weight. A single object might have several measurable attributes of interest.

0C1E3C98D4C34C3A9FEB406148D64D43.description: Identifies parts in relationship to the whole.

3E7AC58797ED4A879F546BECFC46639F.description: Develops increased ability to recognize addition as putting objects together and subtraction as taking objects apart.

B906A06F01B146F0924969515E20AFD2.description: Composing and decomposing numbers; addition and subtraction

828E9BDFE2D946A4A25AF72365925947.description: Number – Operations and the Problems they Solve

2029020CB9864AE29716235F5A9D1EEC.description: Begins to recognize the order of numbers, e.g. before, after and between.

A2A33529B7D0477AB443684A50065CD4.description: Uses comparative words such as more, less, fewer, equal to.

8ED27D0055684FB48BCB235754F1759E.description: Uses one-to-one correspondence in counting objects and matching groups of objects.

E10DAE24A035440DA60BA8BBE13C564B.description: Counting To Tell the Number of Objects

988D803FBACC477A820F2DD3BE0DDDAF.description: Begins to identify number symbols one to ten.

5AAA8841185944479855C681A11A9D88.description: Develops increased ability to counts in sequence to ten and beyond.

E9C7374C52DD449AABD8E20F04C6C5DD.description: Begins to recognize that writing patterns progress from top to bottom, left to right, and words are separated by spaces.

10D6F740D3A24E3981C5847552669237.description: Begins to use functional print in play.

125A2AFAFBB54008946E8B0A11E20E04.description: Demonstrates an understanding that writing relays a message that can be read.

B2232A9096BC4B1BBFF70F222F4FAEEB.description: Progresses from using scribble shapes or pictures to represent ideas, to using letter-like symbols or invented spelling, to copying or writing familiar words such as his/her own name.

CF64CB14989D4708A4207AB0720A6E2C.description: Engages in questioning, reflecting, and relating a story to personal experiences including use of new vocabulary.

0A9F600301044B26AEC7A794691A225C.description: Demonstrates progress in retelling and dictating stories from books and experiences; acts out stories in dramatic play; asks to take home books; goes to the library; and engages in pretend reading with other children.

F98F312D3CD64727A0099475AB4224B1.description: Recognizes story elements such as characters, sequence of events, and theme of a story.

B019D62B56D2497886383C6DD906AFBF.description: Looks through books independently and asks to have books read to them.

80694E8BC26644DCA4411E7A5C36F41A.description: Shows growing interest and involvement in listening to and discussing a variety of fiction and nonfiction books and poetry.

189114A60A7B4A68958FDB8BDAAF6641.description: Recognize words such as his/her name, names of family and friends, and familiar environmental print.

AC926224078341A68703F9DC30BE2581.description: Recognizes a word as a unit of print.

75898FA1846A4C1DBDC73EE2251D1DD8.description: Shows growing awareness of beginning and ending sounds of words.

C7F4AEDD172D4FCEA3BE76BD9B914D28.description: Progresses in recognizing matching sounds and rhymes in familiar words, games, songs, stories, and poems.

70B992E6C70B46ECAA7D558D11F240CE.description: Shows growing ability to hear and discriminate separate syllables in words.

6B07CE3A20F94CAD9E1FBCB9A1E4CF33.description: Listens to and identifies sounds that are in the environment.

ED75E3B12A2A4C12BE09AE4C4A3EFAEE.description: Recognizes and names letters such as those in his/her name, names of family and friends, and those seen in environmental print.

FF0839F41439454886557F282061DF5C.description: Knows that letters of the alphabet are a special category of visual graphics that can be individually named.

20A338768AEF4FB18BA2062A20EEBEF5.description: Develops an awareness of environmental print such as signs, letters, newspapers, lists, messages, and menus.

B8C0FE1EFD9A43D38F029A15A9147708.description: Demonstrates increasing awareness of concepts of print, such as reading moves from top to bottom and from left to right, speech can be written down, and print conveys a message.

81424F763C5747BE8CE2CDFCADBEFFC2.description: Progresses in learning how to handle and care for books; knows how to view one page at a time in sequence from front to back; and understands that a book has a title, author, and illustrator.

43E9BD2C90FB42648DAD749FB045B081.description: Holds book upright and identifies the front and back of a book.

882DFB43D7B949C7B7E0173111D3BF5A.description: Asks questions to get information, seeks help, or clarifies something that is not understood.

C291A7244A3A41F68933D090DF89DD8A.description: Listens to others and takes turns speaking.

168E2F308DBC4E9590699ED689E820E6.description: Comprehends and expands on oral language.

8E90AA5FB8B34F67A6D70FE12717BE50.description: Understands and uses increasingly complex and varied vocabulary/sentences in listening and speaking.

0DA53D7D815E4C5C8C10E50D4CE7AC82.description: Communicates needs and wants through a variety of verbal and symbolic forms.

A63BA995BD88476E924540F9FCDD903B.description: Demonstrates an increasing ability to attend to and understand communication.

E249DA7D5221426FB0DFF18D4BB2230F.description: Utilization of receptive and expressive language for a variety of purposes

CE5A50765EFC44448E70089BB4283CEF.description: Maintains increasing concentration over a reasonable amount of time despite distractions and interruptions.

B38ECA1EEF1548A1B199608ACDE21110.description: Demonstrates increasing ability to set goals and develop and follow through on plans.

2AC839210D634B4186562AE427887A88.description: Persists in and completes tasks, activities, projects, and experiences.

888E8D488A68455895EB19B010412652.description: Approaches tasks and activities with flexibility, imagination, and inventiveness.

20373EA63798450CB1E18E323193E069.description: Develops increased ability to make independent choices.

D53A2C5CAFA545A881F9A55C453F4BD5.description: Participates in a variety of classroom activities and tasks.

FE15FCC2F9C741AB91D83FA655F85EB9.description: Identifies and describes locations and places in their environment.

60375D75E3B54D7FBE67B7E2954B6C53.description: Identifies themselves as a member of groups within a community.

4F518F1CAF6F4A85869B3E2FDD4B8ECD.description: Understands similarities and respects differences among people, such as genders, race, special needs, cultures, language, and family structures.

4AD5F9B878C24461B11190299C5BFF4C.description: Identifies and describes roles and relationships of community members.

70E2F46A30E949CD914C5CCB6A0A2DEF.description: Demonstrates increasing capacity to follow rules and routines and use materials purposefully, safely, and respectfully.

CBCE9EF7F4CA442E90E764265451F6B2.description: Shows empathy and caring for others.

33E62706B37F414CB75CC438E0EEA0ED.description: Develops positive relationships with children and adults.

1A4D3C2EC36B480B94BF000930544BFB.description: Demonstrates progress in expressing needs, wants and feelings appropriately.

092AFF4AACAC445DB6D23434449FD17D.description: Develops growing capacity for independence in a range of activities, routines, and tasks.

B264E4ECF7484C0682B759D6493C900A.description: Demonstrates growing confidence in a range of abilities and expresses pride in accomplishments.

C59D1F10096A46EF94623F403C769E79.description: Describe self by using several basic characteristics.
